  "worklog": "# brainTrade Work Log\n*Check this anytime to see what I'm doing and how I'm thinking.*\n\n---\n## 2026-03-30 19:25 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G Correlation + Monday Trade Review\n\n**Task:** Correlate Fear & Greed with WR. Review first Monday with new filters.\n\n**Findings:**\n1. **F&G is useless as a signal right now** \u2014 ALL 161 trades happened during Extreme Fear (F&G 0-19). No data for other regimes. Can't correlate what doesn't vary.\n2. **Monday results: 3W/2L = 60% WR on 5 trades** (outcomes say 5, but logs show 6 executions). All YES bets at hour 11-12.\n3. **Duplicate trade bug is BACK** \u2014 two trades 7 seconds apart at 11:19 (same 5-min window), two more at 11:38-11:39. Per-window guard is broken.\n4. **Hour 19 completely blocked** \u2014 UP price at $0.540 > max_price $0.535. 46 price blocks today. Our second-best hour is being wasted.\n5. **V3.2 filter blocks NO trades at hour 11** \u2014 \"YES-only, NO=40% WR\". Forces us to wait for negative bias to buy YES.\n\n**My thinking:** Two competing problems:\n- max_price at $0.535 is too tight, blocking our best hours \u2192 should widen to $0.545\n- BUT higher price = higher break-even WR needed (54.5% at $0.545)\n- The duplicate trade bug is more urgent \u2014 it doubles our risk per window\n\n**Decision:** Fix duplicate bug first (P2 priority). Widen max_price to $0.545 with data backing needed. F&G not actionable until we trade in non-fear regime.\n\n**Next P4:** Build BTC volatility regime classifier (ATR-based). More useful differentiator than F&G.\n\n## 2026-03-31 00:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 2] PM Settlement Mystery: $38 Still Pending After 4 Hours\n\n**Task:** Investigate why PM balance hasn't reflected 20h wins.\n\n**Finding:** Balance stuck at $921.75 since 20:40. Expected ~$960.12 after 5W/2L Day 1.\n\n**Investigation:**\n- `get_positions()` returns empty \u2014 no active token holdings visible\n- No `redeem` / `claim` logic in bot code\n- No pending orders\n- PM doesn't charge 47% fees \u2014 settlement must be pending\n\n**Hypothesis:** PM 5-min markets may batch-settle. The 20:15-20:20 window tokens won (BTC went from ~66,574 to ~66,607) but token redemption happens on a delayed schedule. The $38.37 gap exactly matches the expected 20h payouts minus costs.\n\n**Morning session trades settled immediately** \u2014 balance went from $922.45 to $930.37 within the 13:10 restart (3 hours after morning trades). The 20h trades are only 4 hours old \u2014 settlement may take 6-8 hours.\n\n**Action:** Monitor. If balance hasn't updated by 06:00 UTC tomorrow, investigate manual redemption. No impact on trading \u2014 Kelly sizing uses current balance regardless.\n\n**TODO for V5:** Add settlement monitoring \u2014 log balance delta after each expected settlement window, alert if settlement takes >6h.\n\n## 2026-03-30 23:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] Overnight Position Check: HL Stable, PM Settling\n\n**Task:** Check HL positions, funding rates, and PM settlement status before overnight.\n\n**HL Positions (23:38 UTC):**\n| Coin | Direction | Entry | uPnL | Funding/day |\n|------|-----------|-------|------|-------",
